{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17496915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17496915"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T08:59:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T08:59:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1435"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1435"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.6,0.03,0.26,0.06,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1435"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109803"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1435"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1435"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92172"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"7992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12912"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7961"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8547"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35174"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42318"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109803","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109803"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 20-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with painful blisters around and on his lips (Image) and dusky rash across small areas on his limbs. He reports 5-7 days of feeling generally lethargic and malaise. His medical history includes epilepsy for which he has started sodium valproate two weeks ago. On examination he looks unwell, with a blood pressure of 136/88 mmHg, pulse 98/min and temperature 37.8\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stevens Johnson syndrome","Toxic shock syndrome","Bullous pemphigoid","Herpes simplex","Impetigo"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient\u0027s symptoms are consistent with the \u003Cstrong\u003EStevens Johnson syndrome \u003C/strong\u003E(SJS), an acute, serious, potentially fatal adverse drug reaction characterised by fever, flu-like symptoms and a rash on the face and trunk, as well as mucosa. SJS can be caused by a variety of drugs, including antibiotics, NSAIDS, antiseizure drugs, anti-gout, anti-psychotics. In this case, sodium valproate being the causative agent. The lesion may contain macules, diffuse erythema, purpura or blisters.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EToxic shock syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E (TSS) is a toxin-mediated acute life-threatening illness, caused by infection with either \u003Cem\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/em\u003E or group A \u003Cem\u003EStreptococcus\u003C/em\u003E. It is characterised by high fever, rash, hypotension, multiorgan failure and desquamation, initially involving the palms and soles. Myalgia, vomiting, diarrhoea, headache, and neurological abnormalities might also be present.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBullous pemphigoid \u003C/strong\u003Eis an autoimmune blistering disease, usually occurring in people above 50 years of age. Bullous pemphigoid causes severe itch and large, tense bullae, which rupture forming crusted erosions. It typically involves the flexor aspects of the limbs. It may be localised to one area, or widespread on the trunk and proximal limbs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImpetigo \u003C/strong\u003Eis a common and highly contagious bacterial skin infection that mainly affects infants and young children and is characterised by pustules and honey-coloured crusted erosions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHerpes simplex \u003C/strong\u003Eis a common viral infection that presents with localised blistering caused by herpes simplex virus. It can cause blisters and sores around the mouth. Individual vesicles on mucosal surfaces break down forming shallow painful ulcers; They may be covered with a white exudate.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Stevens Johnson syndrome is rare and potentially fatal adverse drug reaction."],"references":["French LE. Toxic epidermal necrolysis and Stevens Johnson syndrome: our current understanding. Allergol Int. 2006 Mar. 55(1):9-16."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92172"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1435"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19565"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19565","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19565"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e4330a14-c7a2-47db-9b46-69c9231c0bb7.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e4330a14-c7a2-47db-9b46-69c9231c0bb7.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92172","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92172"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-26T20:45:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-26T20:45:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1435"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109803"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emed